  <static seed="1398" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/addSubtractRationalExpressions80.pg">
    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{4}{t+4}-\frac{8t}{t^{2}-16}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{4}{t-4}, t\ne -4</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{4}{t+4}-\frac{8t}{t^{2}-16}} 
      \amp = {\frac{4}{t+4}}-\frac{8 t}{(t+4)(t-4)} \\
      \amp = \frac{4\cdot({t-4})}{({t+4})\cdot({t-4})} -\frac{8 t}{(t+4)(t-4)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{4\mathopen{}\left(t-4\right)-8t}}{(t+4)(t-4)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{4t-16-8t}}{(t+4)(t-4)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-4t-16}}{(t+4)(t-4)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-4\mathopen{}\left(t+4\right)}}{(t+4)(t-4)} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{4}{t-4}, t\ne -4}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>{t+4}</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne {-4}</m>.</p>
</solution>
